description.css: If you specify a fade in the worldspawn, or if the engine is running under dx7, then the engine will forcibly fade out props even if fademindist/fademaxdist isn't specified. Numbers smaller than 1 cause the prop to fade out at further distances, and greater than 1 cause it to fade out at closer distances.

description.css: An entity that gives equipment to the player who activates it. To use, add new keys to this entity, where each key is the classname of a weapon/item, and the corresponding value is the number of those weapons/items to give to the player who uses this entity. If the 'Use Only' spawnflag isn't set, then players can just touch this entity to get the equipment.
description.csgo: An entity that gives equipment to the player who activates it. To use, add new keys to this entity, where each key is the classname of a weapon/item, and the corresponding value is the number of those weapons/items to give to the player who uses this entity. If the 'Use Only' spawnflag isn't set, then players can just touch this entity to get the equipment (or the TriggerForAllPlayers input can be used).  If the Strip Player First flag is set, the player will be stripped of all weapons and items (including armor) before being given the items specified in this entity.
